  ANIMALS OF THE WORLD
============================================================

Name:         Axolotl
Scientific:   Ambystoma mexicanum
Class:        Amphibia
Habitat:      Lakes
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     15 years
Weight:       0.3 kg
Status:       Critically Endangered
Fact:         Can regenerate entire limbs, spine, heart, and brain tissue

Name:         Emperor Penguin
Scientific:   Aptenodytes forsteri
Class:        Aves
Habitat:      Antarctic
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     25 years
Weight:       45 kg
Status:       Near Threatened
Fact:         Deepest-diving bird at 565m; male incubates egg 65 days without eating

Name:         Mantis Shrimp
Scientific:   Stomatopoda
Class:        Malacostraca
Habitat:      Tropical ocean
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     20 years
Weight:       0.1 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         Fastest punch in animal kingdom; 16 types of color receptors

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Rationalism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Some knowledge is innate or derivable by reason alone
Philosopher:  Descartes/Spinoza
Example:      Math truths like 2+2=4 are known by reason, not experiment

Concept:      Empiricism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   All knowledge comes from sensory experience; mind is blank slate
Philosopher:  Locke/Hume
Example:      We know fire burns because we felt it, not through pure reason

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Maximize pleasure minimize pain across all sentient beings
Philosopher:  Jeremy Bentham
Example:      Felicific calculus: measure units of pleasure and pain

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Inflation
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: General rise in price levels eroding purchasing power
Formula:    Inflation = (CPI_t - CPI_t-1)/CPI_t-1 x 100
Economist:  Irving Fisher
Example:    2022 US inflation hit 9.1%; Fed raised rates to combat it

Concept:    Opportunity Cost
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Value of next-best alternative foregone when choosing
Formula:    OC = forgone alternative value
Economist:  Bastiat
Example:    Studying means forgoing wages you could have earned working

Concept:    Game Theory
Category:   Economics
Definition: Study of strategic interactions between rational agents
Formula:    Nash equilibrium
Economist:  John Nash
Example:    OPEC cartel coordination; nuclear deterrence strategy

